news.title: PNB Housing Finance to raise $125 million via ECBs
news.para: PNB Housing expects to start corporate business in the next few months to further help in yield and retail business.

news.title: Bhutani Infra's Sancoale project exposes all that’s wrong with Goa planning: GBA
news.para: GBA has also come out in support of former sarpanch Premanand Naik, who is on a hunger strike until the permissions are revoked. “There will be no light for Goa if this game of land conversions and bypassing of building regulations continue,” said GBA secretary Reboni Saha.

news.title: Mumbai-based builder buys Sabarmati riverfront plot for Rs 156.13 crore
news.para: The successful bidder, a leading Mumbai-based real estate company, will now develop a mixed-use commercial building spanning 60,050 sq m, housing upscale offices, co-working spaces, restaurants, retail stores, lounges and a food court.

news.title: Noida authority approves reallocation of data centre plots to IT and ITES sector
news.para: In 2022, on the heels of the Global Investor Summit, the land parcels, spanning over 29,000 sqm, was offered for setting up data centre units under the UP data centre policy, 2021.

news.title: Adani Cement targets 140 MTPA capacity by FY28
news.para: Ambuja Cement, part of Adani Group, which houses all cement assets, is a debt-free company and as of September 2024, cash and cash equivalent for the company was at Rs 10,135 crore, said Kapur.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects acquires 17.45 acres land in Bengaluru for Rs 462 crore
news.para: The acquired land will be planned for residential development spanning approximately 2.68 million sq ft of developable area.

news.title: Co-working operators provided nearly 23,000 desks to GCCs during Jan-Sep 2024: Report
news.para: Real estate consultant Knight Frank India's report 'GCC - Driving India's Real Estate Growth Story' mentioned that the GCCs have emerged as the primary occupiers of flex spaces across the country.

news.title: Abhishek Lodha, family to transfer MDL shares worth Rs 20,000 crore to Lodha Philanthropy Foundation
news.para: "We will soon be transferring shares worth Rs 20,000 crore of MDL to the foundation. An advisory board will be set up in January next year to manage the social initiatives," MDL MD and CEO Abhishek Lodha told PTI.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India reports 68.7% profit drop in Q2 FY25
news.para: HeidelbergCement India had reported a net profit of Rs 35.8 crore in the July-September quarter period a year ago, HeidelbergCement India said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Merlin Group looks to double its revenue over the next 7-8 years
news.para: "We have been growing steadily year on year for the past 40 years. The group is currently developing 40 million square feet that is projected to yield a total sales of Rs 20,000 crore in the coming 7-8 years," Merlin Group managing director Saket Mohta said.

news.title: Anant Raj's net profit increases by 75% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Anant Raj's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 523.75 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 53.67 per cent from Rs 340.83 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Greenply Industries' net profit rises 26.33% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Greenply Industries' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 642.45 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 12.52 per cent from Rs 570.97 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: NBCC to re-develop projects worth Rs 10,000 crore in Goa
news.para: In the first phase, NBCC will execute six projects with an estimated value of more than Rs 1,700 crore. The total plot area of these projects is around 53,000 sq meter, with a built-up area of approximately 1,85,000 sq meter.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's net profit up 11.20% in Q2 FY25
news.para: LIC Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 6,938.31 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 2.55 per cent from Rs 6,765.87 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: SRG Housing Finance's net profit up 25.48% in Q2 FY25
news.para: SRG Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 36.84 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 18.11 per cent from Rs 31.19 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Builders raise over Rs 12,800 crore through QIP during Jan-September 2024: Report
news.para: "To fund their aggressive expansion, developers are turning to IPOs and the QIP route. Their success in these capitalization efforts underscore the sector’s continued ability to attract both retail and institutional investors," said Anuj Puri, chairman of Anarock Group.

news.title: Office space demand to reach 70 million sq ft in 2024: Report
news.para: The demand reached 55.1 million sq ft between January and September 2024, marking a 30% year-on-year (YoY) increase across six cities.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's net profit grows 58.26% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Ajmera Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 204.12 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 38.30 per cent from Rs 147.59 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nilkamal's net profit increases by 30.27% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Nilkamal's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 824.37 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 5.44 per cent from Rs 781.85 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ambuja Cements' net profit dips 52.10% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Ambuja Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 7,890.14 crore in Q2 FY25 as against Rs 7,899.99 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
